ion by the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.Json.DataContractJsonSerializer&gt;</ph>:","pos":[3872,3993],"source":"The .NET Framework 4.7 improves serialization by the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.Json.DataContractJsonSerializer>:"},{"pos":[3995,4061],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Enhanced functionality with Elliptic Curve Cryptography (ECC)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">*</ph>","source":"**Enhanced functionality with Elliptic Curve Cryptography (ECC)***"},{"content":"In the .NET Framework 4.7, <ph id=\"ph1\">`ImportParameters(ECParameters)`</ph> methods were added to the <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Cryptography.ECDsa&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Cryptography.ECDiffieHellman&gt;</ph> classes to allow for an object to represent an already-established key.","pos":[4063,4318],"source":"In the .NET Framework 4.7, `ImportParameters(ECParameters)` methods were added to the <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.ECDsa> and <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.ECDiffieHellman> classes to allow for an object to represent an already-established key."},{"content":"An <ph id=\"ph1\">`ExportParameters(Boolean)`</ph> method was also added for exporting the key using explicit curve parameters.","pos":[4319,4426],"source":" An `ExportParameters(Boolean)` method was also added for exporting the key using explicit curve parameters."},{"content":"The .NET Framework 4.7 also adds support for additional curves (including the Brainpool curve suite), and has added predefined definitions for ease-of-creation through the new <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Cryptography.ECDsa.Create%2A&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Security.Cryptography.ECDiffieHellman.Create%2A&gt;</ph> factory methods.","pos":[4428,4738],"source":"The .NET Framework 4.7 also adds support for additional curves (including the Brainpool curve suite), and has added predefined definitions for ease-of-creation through the new <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.ECDsa.Create%2A> and <xref:System.Security.Cryptography.ECDiffieHellman.Create%2A> factory methods."},{"pos":[4740,4892],"content":"You can see an <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>example of .NET Framework 4.7 cryptography improvements<ept id=\"p1\">](https://gist.github.com/richlander/5a182899895a87a296c21ada97f7a54e)</ept> on GitHub.","source":"You can see an [example of .NET Framework 4.7 cryptography improvements](https://gist.github.com/richlander/5a182899895a87a296c21ada97f7a54e) on GitHub."},{"pos":[4894,4969],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Better support for control characters by the DataContractJsonSerializer<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Better support for control characters by the DataContractJsonSerializer**"},{"content":"In the .NET Framework 4.7, the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.Json.DataContractJsonSerializer&gt;</ph> serializes control characters in conformity with the ECMAScript 6 standard.","pos":[4971,5145],"source":"In the .NET Framework 4.7, the <xref:System.Runtime.Serialization.Json.DataContractJsonSerializer> serializes control characters in conformity with the ECMAScript 6 standard."},{"content":"This behavior is enabled by default for applications that target the .NET Framework 4.7, and is an opt-in feature for applications that are running under the .NET Framework 4.7 but target a previous version of the .NET Framework.","pos":[5146,5375]},{"content":"For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Retargeting Changes in the .NET Framework 4.7<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/framework/migration-guide/retargeting-changes-in-the-net-framework-4-7.md)</ept>.","pos":[5376,5539],"source":" For more information, see [Retargeting Changes in the .NET Framework 4.7](../../../docs/framework/migration-guide/retargeting-changes-in-the-net-framework-4-7.md)."},{"pos":[5565,5575],"content":"Networking","linkify":"Networking","nodes":[{"content":"Networking","pos":[0,10]}]},{"content":"The .NET Framework 4.7 adds the following network-related feature:","pos":[5577,5643]},{"pos":[5645,5700],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Default operating system support for TLS protocols<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept><ph id=\"ph1\">*</ph>","source":"**Default operating system support for TLS protocols***"},{"content":"The TLS stack, which is used by <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Net.Security.SslStream?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> and up-stack components such as HTTP, FTP, and SMTP, allows developers to use the default TLS protocols supported by the operating system.","pos":[5702,5934],"source":"The TLS stack, which is used by <xref:System.Net.Security.SslStream?displayProperty=fullName> and up-stack components such as HTTP, FTP, and SMTP, allows developers to use the default TLS protocols supported by the operating system."},{"content":"Developers need no longer hard-code a TLS version.","pos":[5935,5985]},{"pos":[6015,6022],"content":"ASP.NET","linkify":"ASP.NET","nodes":[{"content":"ASP.NET","pos":[0,7]}]},{"content":"In the .NET Framework 4.7, ASP.NET includes the following new features:","pos":[6024,6095]},{"pos":[6097,6127],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Object Cache Extensibility<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Object Cache Extensibility**"},{"content":"Starting with the .NET Framework 4.7, ASP.NET adds a new set of APIs that allow developers to replace the default ASP.NET implementations for in-memory object caching and memory monitoring.","pos":[6129,6318]},{"content":"Developers can now replace any of the following three components if the ASP.NET implementation is not adequate:","pos":[6319,6430]},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Object Cache Store<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[6434,6457],"source":"**Object Cache Store**."},{"content":"By using the new cache providers configuration section, developers can plug in new implementations of an object cache for an ASP.NET application by using the new <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ICacheStoreProvider<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> interface.","pos":[6458,6654],"source":" By using the new cache providers configuration section, developers can plug in new implementations of an object cache for an ASP.NET application by using the new **ICacheStoreProvider** interface."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Memory monitoring<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[6659,6681],"source":"**Memory monitoring**."},{"content":"The default memory monitor in ASP.NET notifies applications when they are running close to the configured private bytes limit for the process, or when the machine is low on total available physical RAM.","pos":[6682,6884]},{"content":"When these limits are near, notifications are fired.","pos":[6885,6937]},{"content":"For some applications, notifications are fired too close to the configured limits to allow for useful reactions.","pos":[6938,7050]},{"content":"Developers can now write their own memory monitors to replace the default by using the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Web.Hosting.ApplicationMonitors.MemoryMonitor%2A?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> property.","pos":[7051,7235],"source":" Developers can now write their own memory monitors to replace the default by using the <xref:System.Web.Hosting.ApplicationMonitors.MemoryMonitor%2A?displayProperty=fullName> property."},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Memory Limit Reactions<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.","pos":[7239,7266],"source":"**Memory Limit Reactions**."},{"content":"By default, ASP.NET attempts to trim the object cache and periodically call <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.GC.Collect%2A?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> when the private byte process limit is near.","pos":[7267,7440],"source":" By default, ASP.NET attempts to trim the object cache and periodically call <xref:System.GC.Collect%2A?displayProperty=fullName> when the private byte process limit is near."},{"content":"For some applications, the frequency of calls to <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.GC.Collect%2A?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> or the amount of cache that is trimmed are inefficient.","pos":[7441,7598],"source":" For some applications, the frequency of calls to <xref:System.GC.Collect%2A?displayProperty=fullName> or the amount of cache that is trimmed are inefficient."},{"content":"Developers can now replace or supplement the default behavior by subscribing <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IObserver<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> implementations to the application's memory monitor.","pos":[7599,7742],"source":" Developers can now replace or supplement the default behavior by subscribing **IObserver** implementations to the application's memory monitor."},{"pos":[7768,7806],"content":"Windows Communication Foundation (WCF)","linkify":"Windows Communication Foundation (WCF)","nodes":[{"content":"Windows Communication Foundation (WCF)","pos":[0,38]}]},{"content":"Windows Communication Foundation (WFC) adds the following features and changes:","pos":[7808,7887]},{"pos":[7889,7973],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Ability to configure the default message security settings to TLS 1.1 or TLS 1.2<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Ability to configure the default message security settings to TLS 1.1 or TLS 1.2**"},{"content":"Starting with the .NET Framework 4.7, WCF allows you to configure TSL 1.1 or TLS 1.2 in addition to SSL 3.0 and TSL 1.0 as the default message security protocol.","pos":[7975,8136]},{"content":"This is an opt-in setting; to enable it, you must add the following entry to your application configuration file:","pos":[8137,8250]},{"pos":[8462,8528],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Improved reliability of WCF applications and WCF serialization<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Improved reliability of WCF applications and WCF serialization**"},{"content":"WCF includes a number of code changes that eliminate race conditions, thereby improving performance and the reliability of serialization options.","pos":[8530,8675]},{"content":"These include:","pos":[8676,8690]},{"pos":[8694,8827],"content":"Better support for mixing asynchronous 