lse`</ph> (the default), it is possible for clients using <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.ServiceModel.NetNamedPipeBinding&gt;</ph> to attempt to connect to a service listening on a URI that is a substring of the requested URI.","pos":[35748,35975],"source":" With this app setting set to `false` (the default), it is possible for clients using <xref:System.ServiceModel.NetNamedPipeBinding> to attempt to connect to a service listening on a URI that is a substring of the requested URI."},{"content":"For example, a client tries to connect to a service listening at <ph id=\"ph1\">`net.pipe://localhost/Service1`</ph>, but a different service on that machine running with administrator privilege is listening at <ph id=\"ph2\">`net.pipe://localhost`</ph>.","pos":[35978,36192],"source":"For example, a client tries to connect to a service listening at `net.pipe://localhost/Service1`, but a different service on that machine running with administrator privilege is listening at `net.pipe://localhost`."},{"content":"With this app setting set to <ph id=\"ph1\">`false`</ph>, the client would attempt to connect to the wrong service.","pos":[36193,36288],"source":" With this app setting set to `false`, the client would attempt to connect to the wrong service."},{"content":"After setting the app setting to <ph id=\"ph1\">`true`</ph>, the client will always connect to the best matching service.","pos":[36289,36390],"source":" After setting the app setting to `true`, the client will always connect to the best matching service."},{"pos":[36394,36651],"content":"[!NOTE]\n Clients using <xref:System.ServiceModel.NetNamedPipeBinding> find services based on the service's base address (if it exists) rather than the full endpoint address. To ensure this setting always works the service should use a unique base address.","leadings":["","> "],"nodes":[{"content":"Clients using <xref:System.ServiceModel.NetNamedPipeBinding> find services based on the service's base address (if it exists) rather tha