ication configuration file, as follows:"},{"pos":[41745,41777],"content":"Windows Workflow Foundation (WF)","linkify":"Windows Workflow Foundation (WF)","nodes":[{"content":"Windows Workflow Foundation (WF)","pos":[0,32]}]},{"pos":[41779,41910],"content":"In the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)]</ph>, Windows Workflow Foundation has been enhanced in the following area:","source":"In the [!INCLUDE[net_v462](../../../includes/net-v462-md.md)], Windows Workflow Foundation has been enhanced in the following area:"},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Support for C# expressions and IntelliSense in the Re-hosted WF Designer<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> Starting with the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v45](../../../includes/net-v45-md.md)]</ph>, WF supports C# expressions in both the Visual Studio Designer and in code workflows.","pos":[41913,42147],"source":"**Support for C# expressions and IntelliSense in the Re-hosted WF Designer**\n Starting with the [!INCLUDE[net_v45](../../../includes/net-v45-md.md)], WF supports C# expressions in both the Visual Studio Designer and in code workflows."},{"content":"The Re-hosted Workflow Designer is a key feature of WF that allows for the Workflow Designer to be in an application outside Visual Studio (for example, in WPF).","pos":[42148,42309]},{"content":"Windows Workflow Foundation provides the ability to support C# expressions and IntelliSense in the Re-hosted Workflow Designer.","pos":[42311,42438]},{"content":"For more information, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Windows Workflow Foundation blog<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=809042&amp;clcid=0x409)</ept>.","pos":[42439,42563],"source":" For more information, see the [Windows Workflow Foundation blog](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=809042&clcid=0x409)."},{"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">`Availability of IntelliSense when a customer rebuilds a workflow project from Visual Studio`</ph> In versions of the .NET Framework prior to t