=\"p1\">[</bpt>Application Compatibility in 4.6.1<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/framework/migration-guide/application-compatibility-in-the-net-framework-4-6-1.md)</ept>","source":"[Application Compatibility in 4.6.1](../../../docs/framework/migration-guide/application-compatibility-in-the-net-framework-4-6-1.md)"},{"pos":[48411,48499],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>The .NET Framework API diff<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=622989)</ept> (on GitHub)","source":"[The .NET Framework API diff](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=622989) (on GitHub)"},{"pos":[48528,48588],"content":"Cryptography: Support for X509 certificates containing ECDSA","linkify":"Cryptography: Support for X509 certificates containing ECDSA","nodes":[{"content":"Cryptography: Support for X509 certificates containing ECDSA","pos":[0,60]}]},{"content":"The .NET Framework 4.6 added RSACng support for X509 certificates.","pos":[48590,48656]},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]</ph> adds support for ECDSA (Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm) X509 certificates.","pos":[48657,48802],"source":" The [!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)] adds support for ECDSA (Elliptic Curve Digital Signature Algorithm) X509 certificates."},{"content":"ECDSA offers better performance and is a more secure cryptography algorithm than RSA, providing an excellent choice where Transport Layer Security (TLS) performance and scalability is a concern.","pos":[48805,48999]},{"content":"The .NET Framework implementation wraps calls into existing Windows functionality.","pos":[49000,49082]},{"pos":[49085,49301],"content":"The following example code shows how easy it is to generate a signature for a byte stream by using the new  support for ECDSA  X509 certificates included in the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]</ph>.","source":"The following example code shows how easy it is to generate a signature for a byte stream by using the new  support for ECDSA  X509 certificates included in the [!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]."},{"content":"This offers a marked contrast to the code needed to generate a signature in the .NET Framework 4.6.","pos":[49555,49654]},{"pos":[49937,49944],"content":"ADO.NET","linkify":"ADO.NET","nodes":[{"content":"ADO.NET","pos":[0,7]}]},{"content":"The following have been added to ADO.NET:","pos":[49946,49987]},{"content":"Always Encrypted support for hardware protected keys ADO.NET now supports storing Always Encrypted column master keys natively in Hardware Security Modules (HSMs).","pos":[49990,50154],"source":"Always Encrypted support for hardware protected keys\n ADO.NET now supports storing Always Encrypted column master keys natively in Hardware Security Modules (HSMs)."},{"content":"With this support, customers can leverage asymmetric keys stored in HSMs without having to write custom column master key store providers and registering them in applications.","pos":[50155,50330]},{"content":"Customers need to install the HSM vendor-provided CSP provider or CNG key store providers on the app servers or client computers in order to access Always Encrypted data protected with column master keys stored in a HSM.","pos":[50333,50553]},{"content":"Improve <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnectionStringBuilder.MultiSubnetFailover%2A&gt;</ph> connection behavior for AlwaysOn SqlClient now automatically provides faster connection to an AlwaysOn Availability Group (AG).","pos":[50556,50771],"source":"Improve <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnectionStringBuilder.MultiSubnetFailover%2A> connection behavior for AlwaysOn\n SqlClient now automatically provides faster connection to an AlwaysOn Availability Group (AG)."},{"content":"It transparently detects whether your application is connecting to an AlwaysOn availability group (AG) on a different subnet and quickly discovers the current active server and provides a connection to the server.","pos":[50772,50985]},{"content":"Prior to this release, an application had to set the connection string to include <ph id=\"ph1\">`\"MultisubnetFailover=true\"`</ph> to indicate that it was connecting to an AlwaysOn Availability Group.","pos":[50986,51166],"source":" Prior to this release, an application had to set the connection string to include `\"MultisubnetFailover=true\"` to indicate that it was connecting to an AlwaysOn Availability Group."},{"content":"Without setting the connection keyword to <ph id=\"ph1\">`true`</ph>, an application might experience a timeout while connecting to an AlwaysOn Availability Group.","pos":[51167,51310],"source":" Without setting the connection keyword to `true`, an application might experience a timeout while connecting to an AlwaysOn Availability Group."},{"content":"With this release, an application does <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>not<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> need to set <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnectionStringBuilder.MultiSubnetFailover%2A&gt;</ph> to <ph id=\"ph2\">`true`</ph> anymore.","pos":[51311,51465],"source":" With this release, an application does *not* need to set <xref:System.Data.SqlClient.SqlConnectionStringBuilder.MultiSubnetFailover%2A> to `true` anymore."},{"content":"For more information about SqlClient support for Always On Availability Groups, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>SqlClient Support for High Availability, Disaster Recovery<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/framework/data/adonet/sql/sqlclient-support-for-high-availability-disaster-recovery.md)</ept>.","pos":[51466,51713],"source":" For more information about SqlClient support for Always On Availability Groups, see [SqlClient Support for High Availability, Disaster Recovery](../../../docs/framework/data/adonet/sql/sqlclient-support-for-high-availability-disaster-recovery.md)."},{"pos":[51742,51779],"content":"Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF)","linkify":"Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF)","nodes":[{"content":"Windows Presentation Foundation (WPF)","pos":[0,37]}]},{"content":"Windows Presentation Foundation includes a number of improvements and changes.","pos":[51781,51859]},{"content":"Improved performance The delay in firing touch events has been fixed in the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]</ph>.","pos":[51862,51994],"source":"Improved performance\n The delay in firing touch events has been fixed in the [!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]."},{"content":"In addition, typing in a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.RichTextBox&gt;</ph> control no longer ties up the render thread during fast input.","pos":[51995,52125],"source":" In addition, typing in a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.RichTextBox> control no longer ties up the render thread during fast input."},{"content":"Spell checking improvements The spell checker in WPF has been updated on Windows 8.1 and later versions to leverage operating system support for spell-checking additional languages.","pos":[52128,52310],"source":"Spell checking improvements\n The spell checker in WPF has been updated on Windows 8.1 and later versions to leverage operating system support for spell-checking additional languages."},{"content":"There is no change in functionality on Windows versions prior to Windows 8.1.","pos":[52312,52389]},{"content":"As in previous versions of the .NET Framework, the language for a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox&gt;</ph> control ora <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Windows.Controls.RichTextBox&gt;</ph> block is detected by looking for information in the following order:","pos":[52392,52620],"source":"As in previous versions of the .NET Framework, the language for a <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox> control ora <xref:System.Windows.Controls.RichTextBox> block is detected by looking for information in the following order:"},{"pos":[52624,52653],"content":"<ph id=\"ph1\">`xml:lang`</ph>, if it is present.","source":"`xml:lang`, if it is present."},{"content":"Current input language.","pos":[52657,52680]},{"content":"Current thread culture.","pos":[52684,52707]},{"pos":[52710,52869],"content":"For additional information on language support in WPF, see the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>WPF blog post on .NET Framework 4.6.1 features<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=691819)</ept>.","source":"For additional information on language support in WPF, see the [WPF blog post on .NET Framework 4.6.1 features](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkID=691819)."},{"pos":[52872,53134],"content":"Additional support for per-user custom dictionaries\nIn [!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)], WPF recognizes custom dictionaries that are registered globally. This capability is available in addition to the ability to register them per-control.","leadings":[""," "],"nodes":[{"content":"Additional support for per-user custom dictionaries In <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)]</ph>, WPF recognizes custom dictionaries that are registered globally.","pos":[0,175],"source":"Additional support for per-user custom dictionaries\nIn [!INCLUDE[net_v461](../../../includes/net-v461-md.md)], WPF recognizes custom dictionaries that are registered globally."},{"content":"This capability is available in addition to the ability to register them per-control.","pos":[176,261]}]},{"content":"In previous versions of WPF, custom dictionaries did not recognize Excluded Words and AutoCorrect lists.","pos":[53137,53241]},{"content":"They are supported on Windows 8.1 and Windows 10 through the use of files that can be placed under the <ph id=\"ph1\">`%AppData%\\Microsoft\\Spelling\\&lt;language tag&gt;`</ph> directory.","pos":[53242,53401],"source":" They are supported on Windows 8.1 and Windows 10 through the use of files that can be placed under the `%AppData%\\Microsoft\\Spelling\\<language tag>` directory."},{"content":"The following rules apply to these files:","pos":[53403,53444]},{"content":"The files should have extensions of .dic (for added words), .exc (for excluded words), or .acl (for AutoCorrect).","pos":[53448,53561]},{"content":"The files should be UTF-16 LE plaintext that starts with the Byte Order Mark (BOM).","pos":[53565,53648]},{"content":"Each line should consist of a word (in the added and excluded word lists), or an autocorrect pair with the words separated by a vertical bar (\"&amp;#124;\") (in the AutoCorrect word list).","pos":[53652,53835],"source":"Each line should consist of a word (in the added and excluded word lists), or an autocorrect pair with the words separated by a vertical bar (\"&#124;\") (in the AutoCorrect word list)."},{"content":"These files are considered read-only and are not modified by the system.","pos":[53839,53911]},{"pos":[53915,54103],"content":"[!NOTE]\n These new file-formats are not directly supported by the WPF spell checking API’s, and the custom dictionaries supplied to WPF in applications should continue to use .lex files.","leadings":["","> "],"nodes":[{"content":"These new file-formats are not directly supported by the WPF spell checking API’s, and the custom dictionaries supplied to WPF in applications should continue to use .lex files.","pos":[9,186]}]},{"content":"Samples There are a number of <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>WPF Samples<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ms771633.aspx)</ept> on MSDN.","pos":[54106,54209],"source":"Samples\n There are a number of [WPF Samples](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ms771633.aspx) on MSDN."},{"content":"More than 200 of the most popular samples (based on their usage) will be moved into an <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Open Source GitHub repository<ept id=\"p1\">](https://github.com/Microsoft/WPF-Samples)</ept>.","pos":[54210,54371],"source":" More than 200 of the most popular samples (based on their usage) will be moved into an [Open Source GitHub repository](https://github.com/Microsoft/WPF-Samples)."}