g a GUID transaction promoter identifier to the  new <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.EnlistPromotableSinglePhase%28System.Transactions.IPromotableSinglePhaseNotification%2CSystem.Guid%29?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> overload .","pos":[55142,55395],"source":" You do this by specifying a GUID transaction promoter identifier to the  new <xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.EnlistPromotableSinglePhase%28System.Transactions.IPromotableSinglePhaseNotification%2CSystem.Guid%29?displayProperty=fullName> overload ."},{"content":"If this operation is successful, there are limitations placed on the capabilities of the transaction.","pos":[55396,55497]},{"content":"Once a non-MSDTC transaction promoter is enlisted, the following methods throw a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.TransactionPromotionException&gt;</ph> because these methods require promotion to MSDTC:","pos":[55498,55685],"source":" Once a non-MSDTC transaction promoter is enlisted, the following methods throw a <xref:System.Transactions.TransactionPromotionException> because these methods require promotion to MSDTC:"},{"content":"Once a non-MSDTC transaction promoter is enlisted, it must be used for future durable enlistments by using protocols that it defines.","pos":[56068,56201]},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Guid&gt;</ph> of the transaction promoter can be obtained by using the <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.PromoterType%2A&gt;</ph> property.","pos":[56202,56346],"source":" The <xref:System.Guid> of the transaction promoter can be obtained by using the <xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.PromoterType%2A> property."},{"content":"When the transaction promotes, the transaction promoter provides a <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Byte&gt;</ph> array that represents the promoted token.","pos":[56347,56474],"source":" When the transaction promotes, the transaction promoter provides a <xref:System.Byte> array that represents the promoted token."},{"content":"An application can obtain the promoted token for a non-MSDTC promoted transaction with the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.GetPromotedToken%2A&gt;</ph> method.","pos":[56475,56632],"source":" An application can obtain the promoted token for a non-MSDTC promoted transaction with the <xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.GetPromotedToken%2A> method."},{"content":"Users of the new <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.EnlistPromotableSinglePhase%28System.Transactions.IPromotableSinglePhaseNotification%2CSystem.Guid%29?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> overload must follow a specific call sequence in order for the promotion operation to complete successfully.","pos":[56635,56926],"source":"Users of the new <xref:System.Transactions.Transaction.EnlistPromotableSinglePhase%28System.Transactions.IPromotableSinglePhaseNotification%2CSystem.Guid%29?displayProperty=fullName> overload must follow a specific call sequence in order for the promotion operation to complete successfully."},{"content":"These rules are documented in the method's documentation.","pos":[56927,56984]},{"pos":[57017,57026],"content":"Profiling","linkify":"Profiling","nodes":[{"content":"Profiling","pos":[0,9]}]},{"content":"The unmanaged profiling API has been enhanced follows:","pos":[57028,57082]},{"content":"Better support for accessing PDBs in the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ICorProfilerInfo7<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/framework/unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-interface.md)</ept> interface In ASP.Net 5, it is becoming much more common for assemblies to be compiled in-memory by Roslyn.","pos":[57085,57333],"source":"Better support for accessing PDBs in the [ICorProfilerInfo7](../../../docs/framework/unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-interface.md) interface\n In ASP.Net 5, it is becoming much more common for assemblies to be compiled in-memory by Roslyn."},{"content":"For developers making profiling tools, this means that PDBs that historically were serialized on disk may no longer be present.","pos":[57334,57461]},{"content":"Profiler tools often use PDBs to map code back to source lines for tasks such as code coverage or line-by-line performance analysis.","pos":[57462,57594]},{"content":"The <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ICorProfilerInfo7<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/framework/unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-interface.md)</ept> interface now includes two new methods, <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>ICorProfilerInfo7::GetInMemorySymbolsLength<ept id=\"p2\">](../../../docs/framework/unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-getinmemorysymbolslength-method.md)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt>ICorProfilerInfo7::ReadInMemorySymbols<ept id=\"p3\">](../../../docs/framework/unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-readinmemorysymbols.md)</ept>, to provide these profiler tools with access to the in-memory PDB data, By using the new APIs, a profiler can obtain the contents of an in-memory PDB as a byte array and then process it or serialize it to disk.","pos":[57595,58232],"source":" The [ICorProfilerInfo7](../../../docs/framework/unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-interface.md) interface now includes two new methods, [ICorProfilerInfo7::GetInMemorySymbolsLength](../../../docs/framework/unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-getinmemorysymbolslength-method.md) and [ICorProfilerInfo7::ReadInMemorySymbols](../../../docs/framework/unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-readinmemorysymbols.md), to provide these profiler tools with access to the in-memory PDB data, By using the new APIs, a profiler can obtain the contents of an in-memory PDB as a byte array and then process it or serialize it to disk."},{"content":"Better instrumentation with the ICorProfiler interface Profilers that are using the <ph id=\"ph1\">`ICorProfiler`</ph> API’s ReJit functionality for dynamic instrumentation can now modify some metadata.","pos":[58235,58418],"source":"Better instrumentation with the ICorProfiler interface\n Profilers that are using the `ICorProfiler` API’s ReJit functionality for dynamic instrumentation can now modify some metadata."},{"content":"Previously such tools could instrument IL at any time, but metadata could only be modified at module load time.","pos":[58419,58530]},{"content":"Because IL refers to metadata, this limited the kinds of instrumentation that could be done.","pos":[58531,58623]},{"content":"We have lifted some of those limits by adding the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ICorProfilerInfo7::ApplyMetaData<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/framework/unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-applymetadata-method.md)</ept> method to support a subset of metadata edits after the module loads, in particular by adding new <ph id=\"ph1\">`AssemblyRef`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph2\">`TypeRef`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph3\">`TypeSpec`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph4\">`MemberRef`</ph>, <ph id=\"ph5\">`MemberSpec`</ph>, and <ph id=\"ph6\">`UserString`</ph> records.","pos":[58624,58987],"source":" We have lifted some of those limits by adding the [ICorProfilerInfo7::ApplyMetaData](../../../docs/framework/unmanaged-api/profiling/icorprofilerinfo7-applymetadata-method.md) method to support a subset of metadata edits after the module loads, in particular by adding new `AssemblyRef`, `TypeRef`, `TypeSpec`, `MemberRef`, `MemberSpec`, and `UserString` records."},{"content":"This change makes a much broader range of on-the-fly instrumentation possible.","pos":[58988,59066]},{"pos":[59096,59130],"content":"Native Image Generator (NGEN) PDBs","linkify":"Native Image Generator (NGEN) PDBs","nodes":[{"content":"Native Image Generator (NGEN) PDBs","pos":[0,34]}]},{"content":"Cross-machine event tracing allows customers to profile a program on Machine A and look at the profiling data with source line mapping on Machine B. Using previous versions of the .NET Framework, the user would copy all the modules and native images from the profiled machine to the analysis machine that contains the IL PDB to create the source-to-native mapping.","pos":[59132,59496]},{"content":"While this process may work well when the files are relatively small, such as for phone applications, the files can be very large on desktop systems and require significant time to copy.","pos":[59497,59683]},{"content":"With Ngen PDBs, NGen can create a PDB that contains the IL-to-native mapping without a dependency on the IL PDB.","pos":[59686,59798]},{"content":"In our cross-machine event tracing scenario, all that is needed is to copy the native image PDB that is generated by Machine A to Machine B and to use <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Debug Interface Access APIs<ept id=\"p1\">](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ee8x173s.aspx)</ept> to read the IL PDB's source-to-IL mapping and the native image PDB's IL-to-native mapping.","pos":[59799,60120],"source":" In our cross-machine event tracing scenario, all that is needed is to copy the native image PDB that is generated by Machine A to Machine B and to use [Debug Interface Access APIs](https://msdn.microsoft.com/library/ee8x173s.aspx) to read the IL PDB's source-to-IL mapping and the native image PDB's IL-to-native mapping."},{"content":"Combining both mappings provides a source-to-native mapping.","pos":[60121,60181]},{"content":"Since the native image PDB is much smaller than all the modules and native images, the process of copying from Machine A to Machine B is much faster.","pos":[60182,60331]},{"pos":[60356,60379],"content":"What's new in .NET 2015","linkify":"What's new in .NET 2015","nodes":[{"content":"What's new in .NET 2015","pos":[0,23]}]},{"content":".NET 2015 introduces the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph> and .NET Core.","pos":[60381,60473],"source":".NET 2015 introduces the [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)] and .NET Core."},{"content":"Some new features apply to both, and other features are specific to <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph> or <ph id=\"ph2\">[!INCLUDE[net_core](../../../includes/net-core-md.md)]</ph>.","pos":[60474,60653],"source":" Some new features apply to both, and other features are specific to [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)] or [!INCLUDE[net_core](../../../includes/net-core-md.md)]."},{"pos":[60657,60670],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ASP.NET 5<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**ASP.NET 5**"},{"content":".NET 2015 includes ASP.NET 5, which is a lean .NET platform for building modern cloud-based apps.","pos":[60677,60774]},{"content":"The platform is modular so you can include only those features that are needed in your application.","pos":[60775,60874]},{"content":"It can be hosted on IIS or self-hosted in a custom process, and you can run apps with different versions of the .NET Framework on the same server.","pos":[60875,61021]},{"content":"It includes a new environment configuration system that is designed for cloud deployment.","pos":[61022,61111]},{"content":"MVC, Web API, and Web Pages are unified into a single framework called MVC 6.","pos":[61118,61195]},{"content":"You build ASP.NET 5 apps through the new tools in Visual Studio 2015.","pos":[61196,61265]},{"content":"Your existing applications will work on the new .NET Framework; however to build an app that uses MVC 6 or SignalR 3, you must use the project system in Visual Studio 2015.","pos":[61266,61438]},{"pos":[61445,61525],"content":"For information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>ASP.NET 5<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=518238)</ept>.","source":"For information, see [ASP.NET 5](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=518238)."},{"pos":[61529,61548],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ASP.NET Updates<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**ASP.NET Updates**"},{"pos":[61556,61609],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Task-based API for Asynchronous Response Flushing<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Task-based API for Asynchronous Response Flushing**"},{"pos":[61620,61870],"content":"ASP.NET now provides a simple task-based API for asynchronous response flushing, <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.FlushAsync%2A?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph>, that allows responses to be flushed asynchronously by using your language's <ph id=\"ph2\">`async/await`</ph> support.","source":"ASP.NET now provides a simple task-based API for asynchronous response flushing, <xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.FlushAsync%2A?displayProperty=fullName>, that allows responses to be flushed asynchronously by using your language's `async/await` support."},{"content":"In the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v45](../../../includes/net-v45-md.md)]</ph>, ASP.NET added the Model Binding feature that enabled an extensible, code-focused approach to CRUD-based data operations in Web Forms pages and user controls.","pos":[61936,62154],"source":"In the [!INCLUDE[net_v45](../../../includes/net-v45-md.md)], ASP.NET added the Model Binding feature that enabled an extensible, code-focused approach to CRUD-based data operations in Web Forms pages and user controls."},{"content":"The Model Binding system now supports <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task&gt;</ph>-returning model binding methods.","pos":[62155,62260],"source":" The Model Binding system now supports <xref:System.Threading.Tasks.Task>-returning model binding methods."},{"content":"This feature allows Web Forms developers to get the scalability benefits of async with the ease of the data-binding system when using newer versions of ORMs, including the Entity Framework.","pos":[62261,62450]},{"pos":[62461,62557],"content":"Async model binding is controlled by the <ph id=\"ph1\">`aspnet:EnableAsyncModelBinding`</ph> configuration setting.","source":"Async model binding is controlled by the `aspnet:EnableAsyncModelBinding` configuration setting."},{"content":"On apps the target the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph>, it defaults to <ph id=\"ph2\">`true`</ph>.","pos":[62714,62813],"source":"On apps the target the [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)], it defaults to `true`."},{"content":"On apps running on the <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph> that target an earlier version of the .NET Framework, it is <ph id=\"ph2\">`false`</ph> by default.","pos":[62814,62969],"source":" On apps running on the [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)] that target an earlier version of the .NET Framework, it is `false` by default."},{"content":"It can be enabled by setting the configuration setting to <ph id=\"ph1\">`true`</ph>.","pos":[62970,63035],"source":" It can be enabled by setting the configuration setting to `true`."},{"pos":[63043,63074],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>HTTP/2 Support (Windows 10)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**HTTP/2 Support (Windows 10)**"},{"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>HTTP/2<ept id=\"p1\">](http://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP/2)</ept> is a new version of the HTTP protocol that provides much better connection utilization (fewer round-trips between client and server), resulting in lower latency web page loading for users.","pos":[63085,63320],"source":"[HTTP/2](http://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP/2) is a new version of the HTTP protocol that provides much better connection utilization (fewer round-trips between client and server), resulting in lower latency web page loading for users."},{"content":"Web pages (as opposed to services) benefit the most from HTTP/2, since the protocol optimizes for multiple artifacts being requested as part of a single experience.","pos":[63322,63486]},{"content":"HTTP/2 support has been added to ASP.NET in the .NET Framework 4.6.","pos":[63487,63554]},{"content":"Because networking functionality exists at multiple layers, new features were required in Windows, in IIS, and in ASP.NET to enable HTTP/2.","pos":[63555,63694]},{"content":"You must be running on Windows 10 to use HTTP/2 with ASP.NET.","pos":[63695,63756]},{"content":"HTTP/2 is also supported and on by default for Windows 10 Universal Windows Platform (UWP) apps that use the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> API.","pos":[63767,63939],"source":"HTTP/2 is also supported and on by default for Windows 10 Universal Windows Platform (UWP) apps that use the <xref:System.Net.Http.HttpClient?displayProperty=fullName> API."},{"pos":[63950,64374],"content":"In order to provide a way to use the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>PUSH_PROMISE<ept id=\"p1\">](http://http2.github.io/http2-spec/#PUSH_PROMISE)</ept> feature in ASP.NET applications, a new method with two overloads, <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.PushPromise%28System.String%29&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.PushPromise%28System.String%2CSystem.String%2CSystem.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection%29&gt;</ph>, has been added to the <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Web.HttpResponse&gt;</ph> class.","source":"In order to provide a way to use the [PUSH_PROMISE](http://http2.github.io/http2-spec/#PUSH_PROMISE) feature in ASP.NET applications, a new method with two overloads, <xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.PushPromise%28System.String%29> and <xref:System.Web.HttpResponse.PushPromise%28System.String%2CSystem.String%2CSystem.Collections.Specialized.NameValueCollection%29>, has been added to the <xref:System.Web.HttpResponse> class."},{"pos":[64386,64498],"content":"[!NOTE]\nWhile ASP.NET 5 supports HTTP/2, support for the PUSH PROMISE feature has not yet been added.","leadings":["","        >  "],"nodes":[{"content":"While ASP.NET 5 supports HTTP/2, support for the PUSH PROMISE feature has not yet been added.","pos":[8,101]}]},{"content":"The browser and the web server (IIS on Windows) do all the work.","pos":[64509,64573]},{"content":"You don't have to do any heavy-lifting for your users.","pos":[64574,64628]},{"pos":[64639,64813],"content":"Most of the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>major browsers support HTTP/2<ept id=\"p1\">](http://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP/2)</ept>, so it's likely that your users will benefit from HTTP/2 support if your server supports it.","source":"Most of the [major browsers support HTTP/2](http://www.wikipedia.org/wiki/HTTP/2), so it's likely that your users will benefit from HTTP/2 support if your server supports it."},{"pos":[64821,64863],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Support for the Token Binding Protocol<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Support for the Token Binding Protocol**"},{"content":"Microsoft and Google have been collaborating on a new approach to authentication, called the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Token Binding Protocol<ept id=\"p1\">](https://github.com/TokenBinding/Internet-Drafts)</ept>.","pos":[64874,65041],"source":"Microsoft and Google have been collaborating on a new approach to authentication, called the [Token Binding Protocol](https://github.com/TokenBinding/Internet-Drafts)."},{"content":"The premise is that authentication tokens (in your browser cache) can be stolen and used by criminals to access otherwise secure resources (e.g. your bank account) without requiring your password or any other privileged knowledge.","pos":[65042,65272]},{"content":"The new protocol aims to mitigate this problem.","pos":[65273,65320]},{"content":"The Token Binding Protocol will be implemented in Windows 10 as a browser feature.","pos":[65331,65413]},{"content":"ASP.NET apps will participate in the protocol, so that authentication tokens are validated to be legitimate.","pos":[65414,65522]},{"content":"The client and the server implementations establish the end-to-end protection specified by the protocol.","pos":[65523,65627]},{"pos":[65635,65672],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Randomized string hash algorithms<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Randomized string hash algorithms**"},{"content":"The .NET Framework 4.5 introduced a <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>randomized string hash algorithm<ept id=\"p1\">](../configure-apps/file-schema/runtime/userandomizedstringhashalgorithm-element.md)</ept>.","pos":[65683,65837],"source":"The .NET Framework 4.5 introduced a [randomized string hash algorithm](../configure-apps/file-schema/runtime/userandomizedstringhashalgorithm-element.md)."},{"content":"However, it was not supported by ASP.NET because of some ASP.NET features depended on a stable hash code.","pos":[65838,65943]},{"content":"In <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph>, randomized string hash algorithms are now supported.","pos":[65944,66053],"source":" In [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)], randomized string hash algorithms are now supported."},{"content":"To enable this feature, use the <ph id=\"ph1\">`aspnet:UseRandomizedStringHashAlgorithm`</ph> config setting.","pos":[66054,66143],"source":" To enable this feature, use the `aspnet:UseRandomizedStringHashAlgorithm` config setting."},{"pos":[66301,66312],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>ADO.NET<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**ADO.NET**"},{"content":"ADO .NET now supports the Always Encrypted feature available in SQL Server 2016 Community Technology Preview 2 (CTP2).","pos":[66319,66437]},{"content":"With Always Encrypted, SQL Server can perform operations on encrypted data, and best of all the encryption key resides with the application inside the customer’s trusted environment and not on the server.","pos":[66438,66642]},{"content":"Always Encrypted secures customer data so DBAs do not have access to plain text data.","pos":[66643,66728]},{"content":"Encryption and decryption of data happens transparently at the driver level, minimizing changes that have to be made to existing applications.","pos":[66729,66871]},{"content":"For details, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Always Encrypted (Database Engine)<ept id=\"p1\">](/sql/relational-databases/security/encryption/always-encrypted-database-engine)</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>Always Encrypted (client development)<ept id=\"p2\">](/sql/relational-databases/security/encryption/always-encrypted-client-development)</ept>.","pos":[66872,67133],"source":" For details, see [Always Encrypted (Database Engine)](/sql/relational-databases/security/encryption/always-encrypted-database-engine) and [Always Encrypted (client development)](/sql/relational-databases/security/encryption/always-encrypted-client-development)."},{"pos":[67137,67177],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>64-bit JIT Compiler for managed code<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**64-bit JIT Compiler for managed code**"},{"content":"The .NET Framework 4.6 features a new version of the 64-bit JIT compiler (originally code-named RyuJIT).","pos":[67184,67288]},{"content":"The new 64-bit compiler provides significant performance improvements over the older 64-bit JIT compiler.","pos":[67289,67394]},{"content":"The new 64-bit compiler is enabled for 64-bit processes running on top of the .NET Framework 4.6.","pos":[67395,67492]},{"content":"Your app will run in a 64-bit process if it is compiled as 64-bit or AnyCPU and is running on a 64-bit operating system.","pos":[67493,67613]},{"content":"While care has been taken to make the transition to the new compiler as transparent as possible, changes in behavior are possible.","pos":[67614,67744]},{"content":"We would like to hear directly about any issues encountered when using the new JIT compiler.","pos":[67745,67837]},{"content":"Please contact us through <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft Connect<ept id=\"p1\">](http://connect.microsoft.com/)</ept> if you encounter an issue that may be related to the new 64-bit JIT compiler.","pos":[67838,67992],"source":" Please contact us through [Microsoft Connect](http://connect.microsoft.com/) if you encounter an issue that may be related to the new 64-bit JIT compiler."},{"content":"The new 64-bit JIT compiler also includes hardware SIMD acceleration features when coupled with SIMD-enabled types in the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics&gt;</ph> namespace, which can yield good performance improvements.","pos":[67999,68201],"source":"The new 64-bit JIT compiler also includes hardware SIMD acceleration features when coupled with SIMD-enabled types in the <xref:System.Numerics> namespace, which can yield good performance improvements."},{"pos":[68205,68237],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Assembly loader improvements<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Assembly loader improvements**"},{"content":"The assembly loader now uses memory more efficiently by unloading IL assemblies after a corresponding NGEN image is loaded.","pos":[68244,68367]},{"content":"This change decreases virtual memory, which is particularly beneficial for large 32-bit apps (such as Visual Studio), and also saves physical memory.","pos":[68368,68517]},{"pos":[68521,68551],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Base class library changes<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Base class library changes**"},{"content":"Many new APIs have been added around to <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)]</ph> to enable key scenarios.","pos":[68558,68675],"source":"Many new APIs have been added around to [!INCLUDE[net_v46](../../../includes/net-v46-md.md)] to enable key scenarios."},{"content":"These include the following changes and additions:","pos":[68676,68726]},{"pos":[68734,68777],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>IReadOnlyCollection<ph id=\"ph1\">\\&lt;</ph>T&gt; implementations<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**IReadOnlyCollection\\<T> implementations**"},{"content":"Additional collections implement <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Collections.Generic.IReadOnlyCollection%601&gt;</ph> such as <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Collections.Generic.Queue%601&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Collections.Generic.Stack%601&gt;</ph>.","pos":[68788,68979],"source":"Additional collections implement <xref:System.Collections.Generic.IReadOnlyCollection%601> such as <xref:System.Collections.Generic.Queue%601> and <xref:System.Collections.Generic.Stack%601>."},{"pos":[68987,69050],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>CultureInfo.CurrentCulture and CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**CultureInfo.CurrentCulture and CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture**"},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentCulture%2A?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture%2A?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> properties are now read-write rather than read-only.","pos":[69061,69289],"source":"The <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentCulture%2A?displayProperty=fullName> and <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo.CurrentUICulture%2A?displayProperty=fullName> properties are now read-write rather than read-only."},{"content":"If you assign a new <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo&gt;</ph> object to these properties, the current thread culture defined by the <ph id=\"ph2\">`Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentCulture`</ph> property and the current UI thread culture defined by the <ph id=\"ph3\">`Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentUICulture`</ph> properties also change.","pos":[69290,69579],"source":" If you assign a new <xref:System.Globalization.CultureInfo> object to these properties, the current thread culture defined by the `Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentCulture` property and the current UI thread culture defined by the `Thread.CurrentThread.CurrentUICulture` properties also change."},{"pos":[69587,69630],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Enhancements to garbage collection (GC)<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**Enhancements to garbage collection (GC)**"},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.GC&gt;</ph> class now includes <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.GC.TryStartNoGCRegion%2A&gt;</ph> and <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.GC.EndNoGCRegion%2A&gt;</ph> methods that allow you to disallow garbage collection during the execution of a critical path.","pos":[69641,69852],"source":"The <xref:System.GC> class now includes <xref:System.GC.TryStartNoGCRegion%2A> and <xref:System.GC.EndNoGCRegion%2A> methods that allow you to disallow garbage collection during the execution of a critical path."},{"content":"A new overload of the <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.GC.Collect%28System.Int32%2CSystem.GCCollectionMode%2CSystem.Boolean%2CSystem.Boolean%29?displayProperty=fullName&gt;</ph> method allows you to control whether both the small object heap and the large object heap are swept and compacted or swept only.","pos":[69863,70141],"source":"A new overload of the <xref:System.GC.Collect%28System.Int32%2CSystem.GCCollectionMode%2CSystem.Boolean%2CSystem.Boolean%29?displayProperty=fullName> method allows you to control whether both the small object heap and the large object heap are swept and compacted or swept only."},{"pos":[70149,70171],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>SIMD-enabled types<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>","source":"**SIMD-enabled types**"},{"content":"The <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics&gt;</ph> namespace now includes a number of SIMD-enabled types, such as <ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Matrix3x2&gt;</ph>, <ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Matrix4x4&gt;</ph>, <ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Plane&gt;</ph>, <ph id=\"ph5\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Quaternion&gt;</ph>, <ph id=\"ph6\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Vector2&gt;</ph>, <ph id=\"ph7\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Vector3&gt;</ph>, and <ph id=\"ph8\">&lt;xref:System.Numerics.Vector4&gt;</ph>.","pos":[70182,70504],"source":"The <xref:System.Numerics> namespace now includes a number of SIMD-enabled types, such as <xref:System.Numerics.Matrix3x2>, <xref:System.Numerics.Matrix4x4>, <xref:System.Numerics.Plane>, <xref:System.Numerics.Quaternion>, <xref:System.Numerics.Vector2>, <xref:System.Numerics.Vector3>, and <xref:System.Numerics.Vector4>."},{"content":"Because the new 64-bit JIT compiler also includes hardware SIMD acceleration features, there are especially significant performan